column14: * This file includes all county-type areas in the United States.  Not all county-type areas have independent county-level governments (labeled as census counties, independent cities, or other).  Some areas are governed by legally consolidated city-county governments; others are incorporated as independent cities.  Census counties refer to areas with certain types of county offices that are included as part of another government.  Boroughs are unique to Alaska: parishes to Louisiana.  For more information, see Appendix A of Individual State Descriptions at http://www.census.gov/govs/cog/2012isd.pdf.
Offices for Marion County are included in the city government of Indianapolis
Population for NYC combines Bronx, Kings, New York, Queens, and Richmond Counties
